* J. F. Roxburgh (1888–1954), former Housemaster, first Headmaster of Stowe School
* G.O. Smith, sportsman and footballer of the nineteenth century
* Haldane Stewart (1868—1942), former Director of Music. Musician and composer. Organist and choirmaster at Magdalen College, Oxford (1919–1938, 1941–1942). Cricketer for Kent County Cricket Club (1892–1903). Father of concert viola performer, Jean Stewart, and of Lorn Alastair Stewart (Johnnie Stewart), who was creator of &quot;Top of the Pops&quot;.

